<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFABFFB8C6A457D8FE0DF8A6" box="[151,384,1771,1798]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFABFFB8C6A457D8FE0DF8A6" blockId="31.[151,596,1735,1798]" box="[151,384,1771,1798]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
(
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFABFFB8C6AC57D8FEA0F8A5" box="[159,301,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Figs. 23A–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFABFFB8C70B57D8FEF5F8A6" box="[312,376,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">26I–J</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFABFF83C6A45600FE05FF11" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="31" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFABFFB8C6A45600FBACF87D" blockId="31.[151,1437,1843,2014]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFABFFB8C6A45600FE9FF8ED" bold="true" box="[151,274,1843,1869]" pageId="31" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; tarsomere 5 a little longer than tarsomere 1; setal palisade 2/3 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 2 long and 2 short setulae at rear margin; sternite VI reduced to a anterior strip in middle, and enlarging in both sides, bearing 2 long and 2 short setulae; dorsum of oviscape with about 4–5 minute setulae each side.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FF94FF87C6A45479FABBFA26" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" startId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" targetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" targetPageId="32">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FF94FF87C6A45479FABBFA26" blockId="32.[151,1437,1354,1414]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF94FF87C6A45479FED4FAC2" bold="true" box="[151,345,1354,1378]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">FIGURES 23A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFF94FF87C7535479FDD7FAC2" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[352,602,1354,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviflavus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF94FF87C7535479FDD7FAC2" box="[352,602,1354,1378]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Pseudacteon parviflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF94FF87C4535479FD3CFAC1" bold="true" box="[608,689,1354,1377]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FF94FF87C4535479FD3CFAC1" box="[608,689,1354,1377]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FF94FF87C6F45487FC73F9FE" blockId="32.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF94FF87C6F45487FEA8FA6E" bold="true" box="[199,293,1460,1486]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Female.</emphasis>
Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C74F5487FE6EFA6E" box="[380,483,1460,1486]" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
) yellow, with 10–12 setulae. Supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, upper pair being higher on frons than lower fronto-orbital setae. Lower interfrontal seta directly under lower frontoorbital seta. Second row of frontal setae slightly concave, upper interfrontal setae further apart than either is from an upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 brownish yellow and subglobose. Palpus pale yellow, with 4 long setae, apical one longer than maximum width of palpus. Labrum and labella yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FF94FF87C6F4575BFB36F896" blockId="32.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellow. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 0.97: 0.79: 0.71: 0.69: 1, with all five bearing a postero-dorsal setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C35C57BFFF47F96A" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade terminates 2/3 (0.63) along mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C51C5783FC15F96A" box="[815,920,1712,1738]" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 23D</figureCitation>
). Setae below basal half of hind femur a little shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C4DC57E7FCD8F94E" box="[751,853,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 23E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C58657E7FB97F94E" box="[949,1050,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFF94FF87C24457E7FB53F94F" box="[1143,1246,1748,1775]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="0.82">0.82 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFF94FF87C30257E7FA15F94F" box="[1329,1432,1748,1775]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="0.41">0.41 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.50. Costal index 0.36–0.38. Costal ratios 1.19:1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFF94FF87C5D057CBFB2CF8B3" box="[995,1185,1784,1811]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="0.0335" valueMax="0.034" valueMin="0.033">
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFF94FF87C5D057CBFBACF8B2" box="[995,1057,1784,1810]" degrees="0.033" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" precision="55" value="0.033">0.033</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFF94FF87C21257CBFBE2F8B2" box="[1057,1135,1784,1810]" degrees="0.034" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" precision="55" value="-0.034">–0.034</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. Costa with 9–10 dorsal setulae. Alula with 2 setae. Veins brown, membrane brownish gray. Haltere pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FF94FF87C6F45673FDA5F84A" blockId="32.[151,1437,1460,2026]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Abdominal tergites yellow and tergites I–V with sparse minute setulae on posterior margins. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C35C5673FF33F8DF" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 26I</figureCitation>
) reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 2 long and 2 short setulae at rear margin. Venter brown. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C41D56BBFD01F803" box="[558,652,1928,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 26J</figureCitation>
) reduced to an anterior strip in middle, and enlarging on both sides, each bearing 1–2 long and 2–3 short setulae. Oviscape yellowish brown. The dorsum of the oviscape with about 4–5 minute setulae each side (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFF94FF87C78456E3FD91F84A" box="[439,540,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURES 23" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1354,1378]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetId="figure-22@32.[151,1435,179,1327]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 23A–F. Pseudacteon parviflavus sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559611/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Fig. 23F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FF95FF86C6A456A4FAF0F874" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559613" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559613/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" startId="33.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[203,1388,188,1898]" targetPageId="33">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FF95FF86C6A456A4FAF0F874" blockId="33.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF95FF86C6A456A4FED7F80F" bold="true" box="[151,346,1943,1967]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">FIGURES 24A–J.</emphasis>
Tergite VI and sternite VI of females. A–B. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFF95FF86C52856ABFBABF810" authority="Liu et Cai" authorityName="Liu et Cai" box="[795,1062,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisetalis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF95FF86C52856ABFC3AF810" box="[795,951,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">P. quadrisetalis</emphasis>
Liu 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFF95FF86C5D456ABFC74F80F" box="[999,1017,1944,1967]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">et</emphasis>
Cai
</taxonomicName>
; C–D. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFF95FF86C25E56ABFA15F810" authority="Zhang et Liu" authorityName="Zhang et Liu" box="[1133,1432,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trapeziformis">
